<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4d395de0-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s20982"><num value="20982">§ 20982.</num><heading> Assistance for prosecution of cases cleared through use of DNA backlog clearance funds</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id4d395de1-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s20982/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Attorney General may make grants to train and employ personnel to help prosecute cases cleared through use of funds provided for DNA backlog elimination.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id4d395de2-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s20982/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary for each of fiscal years 2007 through 2011 to carry out this section.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id4d395de3-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/248/tVI/s624">Pub. L. 109–248, title VI, § 624</ref>, <date date="2006-07-27">July 27, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/636">120 Stat. 636</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4d395de4-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id4d395de5-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id4d395de6-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s16982">section 16982 of Title 42</ref>, The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section.</p>
</note>
</notes>
